==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-contained Underwater Breathing Apparatus
<hw>Self`-con*tained" Underwater Breathing Apparatus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A portable device to allow divers to breathe while
under water, consisting of one or two tanks of compressed air which are
strapped onto the back of the diver, and are connected by tubing to a
mouthpiece through which the diver receives the air from the tanks at
rate adjustable by a valve; -- called also <altname>SCUBA</altname>,
<altname>SCUBA gear</altname>, or <altname>SCUBA
apparatus</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-contradiction</ent>⟦br⟧
